 Review comment:
   `default_memory_pool()` returns a pointer to a singleton, which I suspect is what's [causing this test to fail](https://ci.appveyor.com/project/ApacheSoftwareFoundation/arrow/builds/27814557/job/vrxo430wmmptaafp#L1637). I believe you can fix it by using `MemoryPool::CreateDefault()` (which explicitly creates a new instance)

